.nh
.TH clankerval 1 "clankerval" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
clankerval \- evaluation runner for clnkr-compatible agents


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBclankerval\fP [\fB--help\fP] [\fB--version\fP] \fIcommand\fP [\fIflags\fP]


.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBclankerval\fP runs evaluation suites owned by a consuming project. It currently supports two commands: \fBrun\fP to execute a suite and \fBinit\fP to scaffold a default evaluations tree.

.PP
Rename note: \fBclankerval\fP is the canonical command name. \fBclnkeval\fP remains supported as a compatibility alias, and both commands accept the same flags.


.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBrun\fP
Run an evaluation suite against the current directory.

.TP
\fBinit\fP
Scaffold an \fBevaluations/\fP directory with the default live-provider example suite.


.SH RUN OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--suite\fP \fIid\fP
Suite identifier to run. Defaults to \fBdefault\fP\&.

.TP
\fB--binary\fP \fIpath\fP
Path to the agent binary under test. When omitted, \fBclankerval\fP builds \fB\&./cmd/clnku\fP from the current source tree when present; otherwise it resolves \fBclnku\fP from \fBPATH\fP\&.

.TP
\fB--evals-dir\fP \fIpath\fP
Evaluations directory. Defaults to \fB\&./evaluations\fP relative to the current working directory.

.TP
\fB--output-dir\fP \fIpath\fP
Output directory for trial bundles and reports. Defaults to the evaluations directory.


.SH EXAMPLES
Run a suite from the current project:

.EX
clankerval run --suite default
.EE

.PP
Scaffold the default live-provider example suite:

.EX
clankerval init
.EE

.PP
Compatibility alias:

.EX
clnkeval run --suite default
clnkeval init
.EE


.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fP
Success.

.TP
\fB1\fP
Error.


